<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-298-572  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 298 572.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>UNIX World  May 1989 v6 n5 p95(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Natural Language comes naturally. (Software Review) (the NaturalLanguage database query language) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Southerton, Alan.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Natural Language Inc's Natural Language 3.0 (NL 3.0) provides anEnglish-language interface to several popular database managementsystems (DBMSs), including Oracle, VAX SQL, Ingres, Sybase,Informix, and ShareBase.andP;  NL 3.0 understands basic, well-organizedEnglish usage, interpreting the input through categorizing theparts of speech, translating these into a 'representationlanguage,' and producing SQL code from identified predicates,objects and descriptions.andP;  A complementary package, NLI Connector,teaches NL 3.0 about new databases.andP;  The firm also offers NLIGateway, which enables transparent access to multiple DBMSs on adistributed processing network.andP;  NL 3.0 runs on a variety ofpopular UNIX-based systems.andP;  Details of the functioning of NL 3.0are described.andP;  The package is $5,000 to $50,000, depending uponthe target system.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Natural Language Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Natural Language 3.0 (Natural language user interface).andO;Topic:     Software PackagesNatural Language InterfacesEvaluationCompatible SoftwareQuery Languages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>